1030@ll>Last Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@1@0@0@0@enterprise I don’t know; but the uncle of our manager was leader of that lot.
1031@fl>First Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@1@0@0@0@“In exterior he resembled a butcher in a poor neighbourhood, and his eyes had a
1032@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@1@0@0@0@look of sleepy cunning. He carried his fat paunch with ostentation on his short
1033@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@1@0@0@0@legs, and during the time his gang infested the station spoke to no one but his
1034@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@1@0@0@0@nephew. You could see these two roaming about all day long with their heads
1035@ll>Last Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@1@0@0@0@close together in an everlasting confab.
1036@fl>First Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@1@0@0@0@“I had given up worrying myself about the rivets. One’s capacity for that kind
1037@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@1@0@0@0@of folly is more limited than you would suppose. I said Hang!—and let things
