1323@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@any conclusion it occurred to me that my speech or my silence, indeed any action
1324@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@of mine, would be a mere futility. What did it matter what any one knew or
1325@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@ignored? What did it matter who was manager? One gets sometimes such a flash of
1326@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@insight. The essentials of this affair lay deep under the surface, beyond my
1327@ll>Last Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@reach, and beyond my power of meddling.
1328@fl>First Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@“Towards the evening of the second day we judged ourselves about eight miles
1329@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@from Kurtz’s station. I wanted to push on; but the manager looked grave, and
1330@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@told me the navigation up there was so dangerous that it would be advisable, the
1331@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@sun being very low already, to wait where we were till next morning. Moreover,
1332@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@he pointed out that if the warning to approach cautiously were to be followed,
1333@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@we must approach in daylight—not at dusk or in the dark. This was sensible
1334@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@enough. Eight miles meant nearly three hours’ steaming for us, and I could also
1335@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@see suspicious ripples at the upper end of the reach. Nevertheless, I was
1336@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@annoyed beyond expression at the delay, and most unreasonably, too, since one
1337@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@night more could not matter much after so many months. As we had plenty of wood,
1338@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@and caution was the word, I brought up in the middle of the stream. The reach
1339@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@was narrow, straight, with high sides like a railway cutting. The dusk came
1340@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@gliding into it long before the sun had set. The current ran smooth and swift,
1341@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@but a dumb immobility sat on the banks. The living trees, lashed together by the
1342@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@creepers and every living bush of the undergrowth, might have been changed into
1343@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@stone, even to the slenderest twig, to the lightest leaf. It was not sleep—it
1344@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@seemed unnatural, like a state of trance. Not the faintest sound of any kind
1345@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@could be heard. You looked on amazed, and began to suspect yourself of being
1346@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@deaf—then the night came suddenly, and struck you blind as well. About three in
1347@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@the morning some large fish leaped, and the loud splash made me jump as though a
1348@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@gun had been fired. When the sun rose there was a white fog, very warm and
1349@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@clammy, and more blinding than the night. It did not shift or drive; it was just
1350@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@there, standing all round you like something solid. At eight or nine, perhaps,
1351@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@it lifted as a shutter lifts. We had a glimpse of the towering multitude of
1352@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@trees, of the immense matted jungle, with the blazing little ball of the sun
1353@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@hanging over it—all perfectly still—and then the white shutter came down again,
1354@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@smoothly, as if sliding in greased grooves. I ordered the chain, which we had
1355@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@begun to heave in, to be paid out again. Before it stopped running with a
1356@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@muffled rattle, a cry, a very loud cry, as of infinite desolation, soared slowly
1357@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@in the opaque air. It ceased. A complaining clamour, modulated in savage
1358@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@discords, filled our ears. The sheer unexpectedness of it made my hair stir
1359@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@under my cap. I don’t know how it struck the others: to me it seemed as though
1360@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@the mist itself had screamed, so suddenly, and apparently from all sides at
1361@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@once, did this tumultuous and mournful uproar arise. It culminated in a hurried
1362@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@outbreak of almost intolerably excessive shrieking, which stopped short, leaving
1363@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@us stiffened in a variety of silly attitudes, and obstinately listening to the
1364@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@nearly as appalling and excessive silence.  ‘Good God! What is the meaning—’
1365@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@stammered at my elbow one of the pilgrims—a little fat man, with sandy hair and
1366@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@red whiskers, who wore sidespring boots, and pink pyjamas tucked into his socks.
1367@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@Two others remained open-mouthed a while minute, then dashed into the little
1368@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@cabin, to rush out incontinently and stand darting scared glances, with
1369@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@Winchesters at ’ready’ in their hands. What we could see was just the steamer we
1370@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@were on, her outlines blurred as though she had been on the point of dissolving,
1371@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@and a misty strip of water, perhaps two feet broad, around her—and that was all.
1372@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@The rest of the world was nowhere, as far as our eyes and ears were concerned.
1373@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@Just nowhere. Gone, disappeared; swept off without leaving a whisper or a shadow
1374@ll>Last Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@behind.
1375@fl>First Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@“I went forward, and ordered the chain to be hauled in short, so as to be ready
1376@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@to trip the anchor and move the steamboat at once if necessary.  ’Will they
1377@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@attack?’ whispered an awed voice. ‘We will be all butchered in this fog,’
1378@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@murmured another. The faces twitched with the strain, the hands trembled
1379@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@slightly, the eyes forgot to wink. It was very curious to see the contrast of
1380@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@expressions of the white men and of the black fellows of our crew, who were as
1381@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@much strangers to that part of the river as we, though their homes were only
1382@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@eight hundred miles away. The whites, of course greatly discomposed, had besides
1383@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@a curious look of being painfully shocked by such an outrageous row. The others
1384@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@had an alert, naturally interested expression; but their faces were essentially
1385@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@quiet, even those of the one or two who grinned as they hauled at the chain.
1386@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@Several exchanged short, grunting phrases, which seemed to settle the matter to
1387@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@their satisfaction.  Their headman, a young, broad-chested black, severely
1388@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@draped in dark-blue fringed cloths, with fierce nostrils and his hair all done
1389@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@up artfully in oily ringlets, stood near me. ’Aha!’ I said, just for good
1390@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@fellowship’s sake. ‘Catch ‘im,’ he snapped, with a bloodshot widening of his
1391@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@eyes and a flash of sharp teeth—‘catch ’im. Give ‘im to us.’ ‘To you, eh?’ I
1392@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@asked; ‘what would you do with them?’ ‘Eat ‘im!’ he said curtly, and, leaning
1393@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@his elbow on the rail, looked out into the fog in a dignified and profoundly
1394@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@pensive attitude. I would no doubt have been properly horrified, had it not
1395@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@occurred to me that he and his chaps must be very hungry: that they must have
1396@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@been growing increasingly hungry for at least this month past.  They had been
1397@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@engaged for six months (I don’t think a single one of them had any clear idea of
1398@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@time, as we at the end of countless ages have. They still belonged to the
1399@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@beginnings of time—had no inherited experience to teach them as it were), and of
1400@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@course, as long as there was a piece of paper written over in accordance with
1401@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@some farcical law or other made down the river, it didn’t enter anybody’s head
1402@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@to trouble how they would live.  Certainly they had brought with them some
1403@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@rotten hippo-meat, which couldn’t have lasted very long, anyway, even if the
1404@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@pilgrims hadn’t, in the midst of a shocking hullabaloo, thrown a considerable
1405@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@quantity of it overboard. It looked like a high-handed proceeding; but it was
1406@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@really a case of legitimate self-defence. You can’t breathe dead hippo waking,
1407@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@sleeping, and eating, and at the same time keep your precarious grip on
1408@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@existence.  Besides that, they had given them every week three pieces of brass
1409@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@wire, each about nine inches long; and the theory was they were to buy their
1410@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@provisions with that currency in riverside villages. You can see how _that_
1411@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@worked. There were either no villages, or the people were hostile, or the
1412@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@director, who like the rest of us fed out of tins, with an occasional old
1413@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@he-goat thrown in, didn’t want to stop the steamer for some more or less
1414@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@recondite reason. So, unless they swallowed the wire itself, or made loops of it
1415@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@to snare the fishes with, I don’t see what good their extravagant salary could
1416@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@be to them. I must say it was paid with a regularity worthy of a large and
1417@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@honourable trading company. For the rest, the only thing to eat—though it didn’t
1418@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@look eatable in the least—I saw in their possession was a few lumps of some
1419@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@stuff like half-cooked dough, of a dirty lavender colour, they kept wrapped in
1420@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@leaves, and now and then swallowed a piece of, but so small that it seemed done
1421@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@more for the looks of the thing than for any serious purpose of sustenance. Why
1422@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@in the name of all the gnawing devils of hunger they didn’t go for us—they were
1423@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@thirty to five—and have a good tuck-in for once, amazes me now when I think of
1424@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@it. They were big powerful men, with not much capacity to weigh the
1425@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@consequences, with courage, with strength, even yet, though their skins were no
1426@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@longer glossy and their muscles no longer hard. And I saw that something
1427@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@restraining, one of those human secrets that baffle probability, had come into
1428@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@play there.  I looked at them with a swift quickening of interest—not because it
1429@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@occurred to me I might be eaten by them before very long, though I own to you
1430@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@that just then I perceived—in a new light, as it were—how unwholesome the
1431@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@pilgrims looked, and I hoped, yes, I positively hoped, that my aspect was not
1432@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@so—what shall I say?—so—unappetizing: a touch of fantastic vanity which fitted
1433@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@well with the dream-sensation that pervaded all my days at that time. Perhaps I
1434@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@had a little fever, too. One can’t live with one’s finger everlastingly on one’s
1435@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@pulse. I had often ‘a little fever,’ or a little touch of other things—the
1436@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@playful paw-strokes of the wilderness, the preliminary trifling before the more
1437@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@serious onslaught which came in due course. Yes; I looked at them as you would
1438@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@on any human being, with a curiosity of their impulses, motives, capacities,
1439@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@weaknesses, when brought to the test of an inexorable physical necessity.
1440@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@Restraint! What possible restraint? Was it superstition, disgust, patience,
1441@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@fear—or some kind of primitive honour? No fear can stand up to hunger, no
1442@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@patience can wear it out, disgust simply does not exist where hunger is; and as
1443@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@to superstition, beliefs, and what you may call principles, they are less than
1444@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@chaff in a breeze. Don’t you know the devilry of lingering starvation, its
1445@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@exasperating torment, its black thoughts, its sombre and brooding ferocity?
1446@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@Well, I do. It takes a man all his inborn strength to fight hunger properly.
1447@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@It’s really easier to face bereavement, dishonour, and the perdition of one’s
1448@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@soul—than this kind of prolonged hunger. Sad, but true.  And these chaps, too,
1449@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@had no earthly reason for any kind of scruple.  Restraint! I would just as soon
1450@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@have expected restraint from a hyena prowling amongst the corpses of a
1451@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@battlefield. But there was the fact facing me—the fact dazzling, to be seen,
1452@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@like the foam on the depths of the sea, like a ripple on an unfathomable enigma,
1453@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@a mystery greater—when I thought of it—than the curious, inexplicable note of
1454@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@desperate grief in this savage clamour that had swept by us on the river-bank,
1455@ll>Last Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@behind the blind whiteness of the fog.
1456@fl>First Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@“Two pilgrims were quarrelling in hurried whispers as to which bank.  ’Left.’
1457@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@‘no, no; how can you? Right, right, of course.’ ‘It is very serious,’ said the
1458@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@manager’s voice behind me; ‘I would be desolated if anything should happen to
1459@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@Mr. Kurtz before we came up.’ I looked at him, and had not the slightest doubt
1460@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@he was sincere. He was just the kind of man who would wish to preserve
1461@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@appearances. That was his restraint. But when he muttered something about going
1462@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@on at once, I did not even take the trouble to answer him. I knew, and he knew,
1463@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@that it was impossible. Were we to let go our hold of the bottom, we would be
1464@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@absolutely in the air—in space. We wouldn’t be able to tell where we were going
1465@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@to—whether up or down stream, or across—till we fetched against one bank or the
1466@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@other—and then we wouldn’t know at first which it was. Of course I made no move.
1467@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@I had no mind for a smash-up. You couldn’t imagine a more deadly place for a
1468@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@shipwreck. Whether we drowned at once or not, we were sure to perish speedily in
1469@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@one way or another. ‘I authorize you to take all the risks,’ he said, after a
1470@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@short silence. ’I refuse to take any,’ I said shortly; which was just the answer
1471@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@he expected, though its tone might have surprised him.  ‘Well, I must defer to
1472@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@your judgment. You are captain,’ he said with marked civility. I turned my
1473@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@shoulder to him in sign of my appreciation, and looked into the fog. How long
1474@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@would it last? It was the most hopeless lookout. The approach to this Kurtz
1475@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@grubbing for ivory in the wretched bush was beset by as many dangers as though
1476@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@he had been an enchanted princess sleeping in a fabulous castle. ‘Will they
1477@ll>Last Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@attack, do you think?’ asked the manager, in a confidential tone.
1478@fl>First Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@“I did not think they would attack, for several obvious reasons. The thick fog
1479@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@was one. If they left the bank in their canoes they would get lost in it, as we
1480@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@would be if we attempted to move. Still, I had also judged the jungle of both
1481@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@banks quite impenetrable—and yet eyes were in it, eyes that had seen us. The
1482@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@riverside bushes were certainly very thick; but the undergrowth behind was
1483@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@evidently penetrable. However, during the short lift I had seen no canoes
1484@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@anywhere in the reach—certainly not abreast of the steamer. But what made the
1485@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@idea of attack inconceivable to me was the nature of the noise—of the cries we
1486@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@had heard. They had not the fierce character boding immediate hostile intention.
1487@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@Unexpected, wild, and violent as they had been, they had given me an
1488@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@irresistible impression of sorrow.  The glimpse of the steamboat had for some
1489@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@reason filled those savages with unrestrained grief. The danger, if any, I
1490@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@expounded, was from our proximity to a great human passion let loose. Even
1491@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@extreme grief may ultimately vent itself in violence—but more generally takes
1492@ll>Last Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@the form of apathy....
1493@fl>First Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@“You should have seen the pilgrims stare! They had no heart to grin, or even to
1494@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@revile me: but I believe they thought me gone mad—with fright, maybe. I
1495@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@delivered a regular lecture. My dear boys, it was no good bothering. Keep a
1496@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@lookout? Well, you may guess I watched the fog for the signs of lifting as a cat
1497@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@watches a mouse; but for anything else our eyes were of no more use to us than
1498@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@if we had been buried miles deep in a heap of cotton-wool. It felt like it,
1499@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@too—choking, warm, stifling. Besides, all I said, though it sounded extravagant,
1500@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@was absolutely true to fact. What we afterwards alluded to as an attack was
1501@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@really an attempt at repulse. The action was very far from being aggressive—it
1502@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@was not even defensive, in the usual sense: it was undertaken under the stress
1503@ll>Last Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@of desperation, and in its essence was purely protective.
1504@fl>First Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@“It developed itself, I should say, two hours after the fog lifted, and its
1505@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@commencement was at a spot, roughly speaking, about a mile and a half below
1506@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@Kurtz’s station. We had just floundered and flopped round a bend, when I saw an
1507@l>Line@nem>Line with No Emphasis@2@0@0@0@islet, a mere grassy hummock of bright green, in the middle of the stream. It
